NavMeshActivatorGD.description: A NavMeshActivator is a component that can be added to any entity with a Transform, and that will cause the computation of NavMesh tiles around the creature in a certain axis-aligned bounding box volume. A follower/attacker should declare only his own size, a followed/attacked should specify all the sizes of the creatures that can attack him.

ActivationZoneSize.description: The size of the axis-aligned square area of NavMesh activated around the entity. While the entity moves in the world, it triggers de computation of the dynamic Navmesh around it in a XY-axis aligned square zone of this size.
ActivationZoneSize.title: Activation Zone Size

SizeLayerMask.description: The NavMeshs containing these size layers will be computed around creatures with this component. The NavMeshActivator does not trigger the computation of all the existing NavMeshes. Through the use of this list, only the ones having these sizeLayerMasks will be computed.
SizeLayerMask.title: Size Layer Mask

NavMeshActivatorGD.title: NavMesh Activator

MinModifParams.title: Min Modif Params

NavMeshMaxHeight.title: Nav Mesh Max Height

NavMeshMaxSize.description: Size of the World, in meters. This is the global size of the world of WiLD. The Navmesh will be sparse, but it needs to know its maximum size in meters.Size above 16km would be problematic, for float precision reasons.
NavMeshMaxSize.title: Nav Mesh Max Size

NavMeshMinHeight.description: Min Height of the NavMesh, in meters. This is the minimum height the DynamicNavMesh can take into consideration. As the DynamicNavMesh takes only ground into consideration, it is the lowest altitude of the deepest pit.
NavMeshMinHeight.title: Nav Mesh Min Height

RecastParameters.description: These recast generation parameters are specific for each creature size. Each DynamicNavMesh, dedicated to a given creature size, will have its own settings.
RecastParameters.title: Recast Parameters

TileMargin.description: Margin around tiles, used for stitching them together. In order to be able to stitch tiles together into a seamless DynamicNavMesh, Recast needs to take a margin into account (extra space around the tile, taking nearby tiles content into account). The bigger the TileSize, the bigger the TileMargin. 10% seems to be a good rule of the thumb.
TileMargin.title: Tile Margin

TileSize.description: The Size on One(1) DynamicNavMesh tile, in meters. The DynamicNavMesh is split into tiles, that are computed/updated dynamically around the creatures with a NavMeshActivator component. Values between 8 and 32 meters are reasonable.

VerticalTolerance.description: The maximum vertical distance acceptable between the NavMesh and the real ground/colliders.

MeshStampers.description: All the meshes used to stamp the DynamicNavMesh. A mesh stamper is a 3D mesh that will be used to generate the main relief of the navmesh.

OffMeshLinks.description: Links between different zones of the navmesh. An OffMeshLink represents a possible shortcut between 2 polygons of the navmesh (one way or symmetric) that can be used by creatures which can perform a given action.

UseSkinnedMeshStamper.description: Uses the PhysicsMeshDeformer and a PhysicsMeshProvider components of the entity to stamp the NavMesh. The provided mesh is used in the shape it has when the stamping/restamping occurs.
UseSkinnedMeshStamper.title: Use Skinned Mesh Stamper

VolumeConstraintStamper.description: VolumeConstraintStamper is used when an Entity has a VolumeConstraint component and needs to stamp a navMesh.
VolumeConstraintStamper.title: Volume Constraint Stamper

ZoneStampers.description: All the convex zones of the DynamicNavMesh with special properties. A zone stamper is a horizontal, 2D, convex zone that will be used to delimit a place in the navmesh's relief with particular properties.
ZoneStampers.title: Zone Stampers

bidirectional.description: Defines whether the link can be used from both ends. If the link is bidirectional, creatures can use the link stating from both side. N.B. the performed action might not be the same depending on the starting side (jump or drop, for example).

capabilitiesAndTags.description: The capabilities the creature must have in order to follow the link, and the tags it can bare on the navmesh. When the creature reaches an active extremity of the link it will perform this action, that will bring it somehow to the other extremity. The tags define area types of this link for the navmesh. Only creatures accapting this typs of tag will be able to use the link.
capabilitiesAndTags.title: And Tags

destination.description: The other extremity of the link. A link will be created between the entity with the NavMeshStamper component to this destination entity.

height.description: The height of the start/end zones of the link. This is used to snap vertically on the navmesh.

offMeshLinkData.description: Data for the current off mesh link
